# Implement Stream CRUD Operations

Implements: [[s-443y|Stream Lifecycle and Management]]

## Objective

Core stream management: create, read, update status, list, and basic queries.

## Data Model

```typescript
interface Stream {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  agentId: string;
  baseCommit: string;
  parentStream: string | null;
  status: StreamStatus;
  createdAt: number;
  updatedAt: number;
  mergedInto: string | null;
  enableStackedReview: boolean;
  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;
}

type StreamStatus = 'active' | 'paused' | 'merged' | 'abandoned';
```

## Tasks

- [ ] Implement `createStream()`:
  ```typescript
  function createStream(options: {
    name: string;
    agentId: string;
    base?: string;
    parentStream?: string;
    enableStackedReview?: boolean;
  }): string {
    // 1. Generate unique stream ID (8-char hex)
    // 2. Resolve base to commit hash
    // 3. Create git branch stream/{id} at base
    // 4. Record in database
    // 5. Return streamId
  }
  ```

- [ ] Implement `getStream()`:
  - Fetch by ID
  - Return Stream or undefined

- [ ] Implement `listStreams()`:
  ```typescript
  function listStreams(filter?: {
    status?: StreamStatus;
    agentId?: string;
  }): Stream[];
  ```

- [ ] Implement `updateStreamStatus()`:
  - Transition between states
  - Update `updatedAt` timestamp

- [ ] Implement `abandonStream()`:
  - Set status to abandoned
  - Record reason in metadata
  - Keep git branch (for recovery)

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Can create stream from main or specific commit
- [ ] Git branch `stream/{id}` created correctly
- [ ] Status transitions work
- [ ] Listing with filters works
- [ ] Tests cover happy path and edge cases

# Implement Database Layer

Implements: [[s-9vjj|Concurrency Model and Coordination]]

## Objective

Set up better-sqlite3 with WAL mode for concurrent-safe metadata storage.

## Tasks

- [ ] Create Database wrapper class:
  ```typescript
  import Database from 'better-sqlite3';

  export class DataplaneDB {
    private db: Database.Database;

    constructor(path: string) {
      this.db = new Database(path);
      this.db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');
      this.initSchema();
    }

    transaction<T>(fn: () => T): T {
      return this.db.transaction(fn)();
    }

    close(): void {
      this.db.close();
    }
  }
  ```

- [ ] Define table schemas:
  ```sql
  CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS streams (
    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    name TEXT NOT NULL,
    agent_id TEXT NOT NULL,
    base_commit TEXT NOT NULL,
    parent_stream TEXT,
    status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'active',
    created_at REAL NOT NULL,
    updated_at REAL NOT NULL,
    merged_into TEXT,
    enable_stacked_review INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    metadata TEXT DEFAULT '{}'
  );

  CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS operations (...);
  CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS worktrees (...);
  CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS stream_locks (...);
  CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS stream_guards (...);
  ```

- [ ] Implement typed query helpers:
  ```typescript
  interface QueryHelpers<T> {
    get(id: string): T | undefined;
    getBy(where: Partial<T>): T | undefined;
    list(where?: Partial<T>): T[];
    insert(row: Omit<T, 'id'>): string;
    update(id: string, changes: Partial<T>): void;
    delete(id: string): void;
  }
  ```

- [ ] Verify WAL mode is enabled and concurrent writes work

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Database creates `.db` file with WAL mode
- [ ] `-wal` and `-shm` files created during operation
- [ ] Multiple connections can write concurrently
- [ ] Transactions rollback on exception
- [ ] Tests pass for CRUD operations

# Implement Operation Logging

Implements: [[s-9brh|Multi-Agent Git Tracking System]]

## Objective

Record all mutations to repository state for audit trail and rollback support.

## Data Model

```typescript
interface Operation {
  id: string;
  streamId: string;
  agentId: string;
  opType: OperationType;
  beforeState: string;      // Commit hash before
  afterState: string;       // Commit hash after
  parentOps: string[];      // Parent operation IDs
  timestamp: number;
  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;
}

type OperationType =
  | 'commit'
  | 'amend'
  | 'rebase'
  | 'merge'
  | 'cherry_pick'
  | 'rollback'
  | 'reset';
```

## Tasks

- [ ] Implement `recordOperation()`:
  ```typescript
  function recordOperation(options: {
    streamId: string;
    agentId: string;
    opType: OperationType;
    beforeState: string;
    afterState: string;
    parentOps?: string[];
    metadata?: Record<string, unknown>;
  }): string;  // Returns operation ID
  ```

- [ ] Implement `getOperation()`:
  - Fetch by ID
  - Return Operation or undefined

- [ ] Implement `getOperations()`:
  ```typescript
  function getOperations(filter?: {
    streamId?: string;
    agentId?: string;
    opType?: OperationType;
    since?: number;
  }): Operation[];
  ```

- [ ] Implement `getLatestOperation()`:
  - Get most recent operation for a stream

- [ ] Implement `getOperationChain()`:
  - Walk parentOps to build operation history
  - Return ordered list from oldest to newest

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Operations recorded with correct before/after states
- [ ] Parent chain correctly links operations
- [ ] Filtering and querying works
- [ ] Tests verify DAG structure

